    "top_event": "Personnel struck by swinging bolt during equipment change-out",
    "incident_type": "Injury - Laceration and dental damage",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured person reported to Rig Medic",
      "Injured person evaluated by Rig Medic",
      "Injured person sent ashore via helicopter for further medical attention",
      "Injured person received stitches to bottom lip",
      "Injured person evaluated by dentist for chipped teeth"
    ],
    "summary": "During a Stab-Rite equipment change-out operation on the H&P 205 rig, an injured person was cutting all-thread bolts using an air-operated band saw. After removing nine bolts, the tenth bolt snapped while being cut. The snapping bolt caused the top metal plate of the Stab-Rite bracket to shift approximately three inches, swinging the bolt vertically and striking the injured person's mouth. The injured person sustained a laceration to the bottom lip and chipped front teeth.",
